In the course the morphological structure of a word and the grammatical categories are treated. The parts of speech, declining, comparing, and conjugating, also conjugations and declinations are studied throughout the course.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give an overview of the morphological level and to introduce basic theoretical approaches to word form research. To discuss basic concepts and morphological categories of Standard Estonian.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course the student
- knows basic concepts of morphology
- knows Estonian morphological categories
- can analyze and synthesize the morphological structure of Estonian word forms
- can define parts of speech in Estonian
- knows the types of Estonian gradation
- knows Estonian inflection types.
